ECD teachers from Budalangi constituency, Bunyala subcounty, have told political aspirants to stop taking them for a ride.They said some aspirants summon them for a meeting only to leave them at the venue stranded without fare back home.The teachers spoke to the Star on Tuesday at Sibuka Primary School, Bunyala North ward.They said 54 teachers were left stranded recently by an ODM parliamentary aspirant, who later sent them Sh3,000. Another 96 were left stranded at Budalang'i Primary School. They were rescued by an MCA aspirant who gave them Sh2,000.